  "text": "To ease the autocorrelation problem arising from the original least square fitting, the first-order autoregressive and first-order moving average (ARMA(1, 1)) was applied instead of the commonly used first-order autoregressive (AR(1)) model. As pointed out by Foster and Brown (2015), its advantage over the AR(1) model is its capability to resolve the underestimation of standard errors. All statistical values in our study were computed for a two-tailed Student t-test at a 95% significance interval. Note that the corrected confidence intervals are associated with smoothed data and might consist of unavoidable dominant uncertainties, including observational errors in the satellite orbit corrections applied [CITATION_1] .",
